Description: Fragment of pseudo-bifid handle of a Rhodian fractional pottery transport amphora to sharp turn. Clay fine buff-brown. Circular stamp with Heliod head symbol.
Curator's comments: Trimmed. There are similar stamps on lagynoi in the Benaki collection, Graeco-Roman Museum, Alexandria.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1206)
